if there are any errors in the page rendering, e.g. a bad plugin that causes page is not rendered but a error message occurs (something like)
{code}
<div id="main-content" class="wiki-content">                           
        <div class="error">Error: Illegal group reference</div>
</div>
{code}

the page still sends a HTTP Return code 200 "all ok"

In contrast, if a page is not found, you correctly return 404.

So I suggest you should sent a HTTP error code (from 500er series?) instead of 200 if there are any errors.
This will also improve crawlers, indexing appliances and even plugin tests to detect errors.

